@fredhebert8592 You're looking for a working governor mechanism, of either type... one that keeps the engine at a set RPM by varying the throttle, or one that changes gear ratios on a CVT to assist keeping a given output RPM. 

If you want to get handsy with it, think about combining a go-cart CVT unit with a 'Centrifugal_governor' (which I put in quotes so you can cut and paste into wikipedia).

EDIT: And don't expect too much from it, you can only really ever expect to get 750 watts from a 1hp motor, and that's with 100% efficiency (i.e. impossible), 50% would be fantastic efficiency for a homebrew setup (375 watts).
